-- Zanaco of Zambia Says First-Half Profit Advances 46% on Increase in Income
-- Brian Latham
-- 2010-09-20T11:45:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/zanaco-of-zambia-says-its-first-half-profit-advances-46-on-income-rise.html

          
          
             Zambia National Commercial Bank Plc 
said profit rose 46 percent in the half-year through June on
higher non-interest income.  
 Net income increased to 49.4 billion kwacha from 33.8
billion kwacha a year earlier, the company said today in a
statement on its website. Total income rose 12 percent to 242.3
billion kwacha and non-interest income increased 36 percent to
98.2 billion kwacha.  
